text: Nenad Stekić (; 7 March 1951 – 18 July 2021) was a Serbian and Yugoslav long jumper. He was best known for his European record of 8.45 metres. He participated in the 1976, 1980 and 1984 Summer Olympics. He won two silver medals at the European Athletics Championships in 1974 and 1978. Stekić died on 18 July 2021 in Belgrade at the age of 70.Preminuo Nenad Stekić, 18. 7. 2021. ==References== Category:1951 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympians for Yugoslavia Category:Long jumpers Category:Yugoslavian athletes
